61.
Two pointers two-pass approach example:
The main trick is to use a two-pass approach to efficiently calculate the shortest distances:
Left to Right Pass:
Calculate the shortest distance to the target character encountered so far.
Right to Left Pass:
Refine the distances by considering the distances to the target character encountered from the right side.

